Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the potatoes.

Remove the @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} and @unsalted butter{30%g} from your
fridge to allow them to come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes and cook until you can easily
slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{1}. Finely chop the @black garlic cloves{1}.

Add the chopped black garlic into a small #bowl{} with the butter and mash with a
#fork{} until combined. Season with @salt{} and a pinch of @chilli flakes{1/4%tsp}
(careful, they're hot - add less if you don't like heat), then set the garlic butter
aside.

== Salad Dressing ==

In a medium bowl, combine the @Dijon mustard{1/2%tsp} and @red wine vinegar{12%ml},
then gradually mix in the @olive oil{2%tbsp} with a fork or #whisk{} until well
combined.

Season with @salt{} and @freshly ground black pepper{}, then set the salad dressing
aside for now.

== Steak ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with
@salt{} and @freshly ground black pepper{}.

When the oil is hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned, ~{1%minute}
on each side.

Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want
them medium-rare.

> Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more well done. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer the steaks to a #plate{} and spoon over the black garlic
butter. Cover loosely with #foil{} and allow to rest for a couple of ~{2%minutes}.

== Spring Onion Mash ==

While the steaks rest, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} once cooked and return to
the pan, off the heat.

Add a @knob of butter{1%small} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash until smooth with a
#potato masher{}. Season with @salt{} and @freshly ground black pepper{}, then stir
through the spring onion.

== To Serve ==

When ready to serve, slice the steaks widthways into 1cm slices.

Share the mash between your plates, then plate up the steak alongside, spooning over
the melted black garlic butter.

Toss the @pea shoots{40%g} in the mustard dressing and add to your plates. Sprinkle
with @?chilli flakes{} to finish. Enjoy!